<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880224-0119 </DOCNO><HL> CompuTrac Plans Buy-Back </HL><SO> </SO><CO> LLB </CO><IN> BBK </IN><DATELINE> DALLAS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   CompuTrac Inc. said its board authorized a program to purchase from time to time as many as 600,000 of its six million common shares outstanding in the open market or through negotiated transactions.    CompuTrac provides computer systems designed specifically for the legal profession and information retrieval systems for general corporate use.    Its shares closed yesterday at $3, up 37.5 cents, in American Stock Exchange composite trading. </TEXT></DOC>